tutorial_lessons.title: Understanding Forks
tutorial_lessons.content_data:
{"type":"theory","slides":[{"title":"What is a Fork?","content":"

A fork is when one piece attacks two or more enemy pieces at the same time.<\/p>"},{"title":"Knight Forks","content":"

Knights are especially good at forks because of their unique L-shaped movement.<\/p>"}]}

interactive_lesson_stages.title: How the Pawn Moves
interactive_lesson_stages.instruction_text: The pawn moves forward one square at a time. On its first move, it can move two squares! Try moving the white pawn.
interactive_lesson_stages.hints: ["Click on the pawn on d2","You can move it to d3 or d4 (first move special)","Pawns can only move forward, never backward"]
interactive_lesson_stages.feedback_messages: {"correct":"Perfect! Pawns move forward.","incorrect":"Try moving the pawn forward only.","hint":"Pawns move straight ahead."}

interactive_lesson_stages.title: How the Pawn Captures
interactive_lesson_stages.instruction_text: Pawns capture diagonally! Capture the black pawn using your white pawn.
interactive_lesson_stages.hints: ["Pawns capture one square diagonally forward","Your e4 pawn can capture on d5","Pawns don't capture straight ahead"]
interactive_lesson_stages.feedback_messages: {"correct":"Excellent! Pawns capture diagonally.","incorrect":"Remember: pawns capture diagonally.","hint":"Try moving e4 to d5."}

interactive_lesson_stages.title: Pawn Quiz
interactive_lesson_stages.instruction_text: Quick quiz: Which square can this pawn move to?
interactive_lesson_stages.hints: ["First move can be 1 or 2 squares","This pawn hasn't moved yet","Try e3 or e4"]
interactive_lesson_stages.feedback_messages: {"correct":"Great job! You understand pawn movement!","incorrect":"Review: pawns move forward 1-2 squares on first move.","hint":"This is the pawn's first move."}

interactive_lesson_stages.title: How the Rook Moves
interactive_lesson_stages.instruction_text: The rook moves in straight lines - horizontally or vertically, any number of squares! Try moving the white rook.
interactive_lesson_stages.goals: [{"type":"move_piece","description":"Move the rook along a rank or file"}]
interactive_lesson_stages.hints: ["Rooks move horizontally or vertically","They can move any number of squares","Try moving along the 4th rank or d-file"]
interactive_lesson_stages.feedback_messages: {"correct":"Perfect! Rooks move in straight lines.","incorrect":"Rooks can only move horizontally or vertically.","hint":"Think of a plus sign (+) pattern."}

interactive_lesson_stages.title: Rook Captures
interactive_lesson_stages.instruction_text: Capture the black pawn with your rook!
interactive_lesson_stages.hints: ["The rook on d4 can capture on d5","Rooks capture by landing on the enemy piece","Move along the d-file"]
interactive_lesson_stages.feedback_messages: {"correct":"Excellent capture!","incorrect":"Try moving the rook vertically to d5.","hint":"Rooks move in straight lines to capture."}

interactive_lesson_stages.title: How the Knight Moves
interactive_lesson_stages.instruction_text: The knight moves in an "L" shape - 2 squares in one direction and 1 square perpendicular. It can jump over other pieces! Try it.
interactive_lesson_stages.hints: ["Knights move in an L-shape: 2+1 or 1+2","From d4, the knight can reach 8 squares","Try c2, e2, f3, f5, e6, c6, b5, or b3"]
interactive_lesson_stages.feedback_messages: {"correct":"Great! Knights move in an L-shape.","incorrect":"Knights must move in an L-shape (2+1).","hint":"Think of drawing an L on the board."}

interactive_lesson_stages.title: Knight Jumping
interactive_lesson_stages.instruction_text: Knights can jump over pieces! Move the knight over the pawn to capture the black pawn on e6.
interactive_lesson_stages.hints: ["Knights are the only piece that can jump","The white pawn on d3 doesn't block the knight","Move from d4 to e6 in an L-shape to capture"]
interactive_lesson_stages.feedback_messages: {"correct":"Perfect! Knights can jump over pieces.","incorrect":"Use the knight's jumping ability.","hint":"Move to e6 in an L-shape."}

interactive_lesson_stages.title: Meet the Bishop! ♗
interactive_lesson_stages.instruction_text: This is the BISHOP ♗. The bishop moves DIAGONALLY any number of squares! It slides along diagonal lines like this: ↗ ↖ ↘ ↙. Notice how all the arrows point diagonally from the bishop in an X pattern. Each bishop stays on its starting color forever!
interactive_lesson_stages.hints: ["Look at the arrows - they all point diagonally!","Bishops move in 4 diagonal directions","Think of an X pattern from the bishop","This bishop is on a light square and stays on light squares forever"]
interactive_lesson_stages.feedback_messages: {"correct":"Perfect! You moved the bishop diagonally! Bishops move in an X pattern.","incorrect":"Remember: bishops only move diagonally. Try following one of the arrows!","hint":"Bishops move diagonally - like an X from their position."}

interactive_lesson_stages.title: Your Turn - Move the Bishop!
interactive_lesson_stages.instruction_text: Now YOU try! Click the white bishop and move it to ANY diagonal square. The arrows show some example moves you can make. All diagonal moves are correct!
interactive_lesson_stages.goals: [{"type":"move_piece","piece":"bishop","description":"Move the bishop to any diagonal square","feedback_success":"Excellent! You moved the bishop diagonally! \u2728","feedback_fail":"Remember: bishops only move diagonally. Look at the arrows and try again!"}]
interactive_lesson_stages.hints: ["Click on the bishop at d4","Bishops move diagonally only - no straight moves!","Try moving to any highlighted square","All diagonal moves are correct - pick any direction!"]
interactive_lesson_stages.feedback_messages: {"correct":"Excellent! You moved the bishop diagonally! \u2728","incorrect":"Remember: bishops only move diagonally. Look at the arrows and try again!","hint":"Think of an X pattern from the bishop - pick any diagonal direction."}

interactive_lesson_stages.title: Bishop Captures ⚔️
interactive_lesson_stages.instruction_text: Great! Now let's learn how bishops capture. Bishops capture by landing on enemy pieces. Move your bishop to capture the black pawn!
interactive_lesson_stages.hints: ["The pawn is on f6 - can the bishop reach it diagonally?","Follow the diagonal path: d4 \u2192 e5 \u2192 f6","Bishops capture by landing on the enemy piece","Move the bishop from d4 to f6 to capture!"]
interactive_lesson_stages.feedback_messages: {"correct":"Perfect capture! \ud83c\udfaf You understand how bishops move and capture! The bishop moved diagonally and captured the pawn.","incorrect":"Not quite. Move the bishop diagonally to f6 to capture the pawn.","hint":"Follow the red arrow - move diagonally from d4 to f6."}

interactive_lesson_stages.title: How the Queen Moves
interactive_lesson_stages.instruction_text: The queen is the most powerful piece! It combines the moves of the rook and bishop - moving horizontally, vertically, or diagonally, any number of squares.
interactive_lesson_stages.hints: ["The queen moves like a rook + bishop combined","She can move in 8 directions","Try any horizontal, vertical, or diagonal move"]
interactive_lesson_stages.feedback_messages: {"correct":"Perfect! The queen is very powerful.","incorrect":"Queens move like rooks + bishops.","hint":"The queen can move in any straight line."}

interactive_lesson_stages.title: Queen Captures
interactive_lesson_stages.instruction_text: Capture the black pawn with your queen!
interactive_lesson_stages.hints: ["The queen can capture diagonally like a bishop","Or horizontally\/vertically like a rook","Find the path to f6"]
interactive_lesson_stages.feedback_messages: {"correct":"Excellent! The queen is a powerful attacker.","incorrect":"Use the queen's flexible movement.","hint":"Move diagonally to f6."}

interactive_lesson_stages.title: How the King Moves
interactive_lesson_stages.instruction_text: The king is the most important piece! It moves one square in any direction. If your king is captured, you lose the game.
interactive_lesson_stages.hints: ["The king moves one square at a time","It can move in any direction","Try moving to any adjacent square"]
interactive_lesson_stages.feedback_messages: {"correct":"Good! Remember to protect your king.","incorrect":"The king moves only one square.","hint":"Move to any adjacent square."}

interactive_lesson_stages.title: King Safety
interactive_lesson_stages.instruction_text: Your king is in check from the rook! You must move it to a safe square where it won't be attacked.
interactive_lesson_stages.hints: ["The rook on e8 attacks along the e-file","Find a square not on the e-file","Try d1, d2, f1, or f2"]
interactive_lesson_stages.feedback_messages: {"correct":"Safe! Always protect your king.","incorrect":"That square is still under attack.","hint":"Move away from the e-file."}

interactive_lesson_stages.title: Kingside Castling
interactive_lesson_stages.instruction_text: Castling is a special move! To castle kingside, move your king two squares toward the rook on h1. The rook will automatically jump to the other side of the king.
interactive_lesson_stages.hints: ["The king must not have moved yet","The rook must not have moved yet","There must be no pieces between them","Drag your king two squares to the right (g1)"]
interactive_lesson_stages.feedback_messages: {"correct":"Perfect! You castled kingside. This protects your king and activates your rook.","incorrect":"Remember: move the king two squares toward the rook.","hint":"Drag the king from e1 to g1."}

interactive_lesson_stages.title: Queenside Castling
interactive_lesson_stages.instruction_text: Now try castling queenside! Move your king two squares toward the rook on a1.
interactive_lesson_stages.hints: ["Castling queenside is longer","Move the king two squares to the left","The rook will jump over to d1","Drag your king from e1 to c1"]
interactive_lesson_stages.feedback_messages: {"correct":"Excellent! Queenside castling complete.","incorrect":"Move the king two squares toward the a-file rook.","hint":"Drag the king from e1 to c1."}

interactive_lesson_stages.title: When You Cannot Castle
interactive_lesson_stages.instruction_text: You cannot castle when your king is in check! Move your king to safety instead.
interactive_lesson_stages.hints: ["Your king is in check from the rook on e3","You cannot castle while in check","Move your king to a safe square","Try moving to d1, d2, f1, or f2"]
interactive_lesson_stages.feedback_messages: {"correct":"Good! Remember: you cannot castle when in check.","incorrect":"You cannot castle while in check. Move to safety.","hint":"Get out of check first."}

interactive_lesson_stages.title: En Passant Setup
interactive_lesson_stages.instruction_text: En passant is a special pawn capture! When an enemy pawn moves two squares forward from its starting position and lands beside your pawn, you can capture it as if it only moved one square.
interactive_lesson_stages.hints: ["The black pawn just moved from d7 to d5","It landed beside your white pawn on e5","You can capture it en passant by moving to d6","This capture is only available immediately after the pawn's two-square move"]
interactive_lesson_stages.feedback_messages: {"correct":"Great! You understand the en passant setup.","incorrect":"","hint":"Study the position - the black pawn just moved two squares."}

interactive_lesson_stages.title: Execute En Passant
interactive_lesson_stages.instruction_text: Now try it! Capture the black pawn en passant.
interactive_lesson_stages.hints: ["Move your e5 pawn diagonally to d6","This will capture the pawn on d5","Even though you move to d6, you capture the pawn on d5"]
interactive_lesson_stages.feedback_messages: {"correct":"Perfect! You captured en passant! This is a unique pawn move.","incorrect":"Move your pawn from e5 to d6 to capture en passant.","hint":"Move diagonally to d6, even though the pawn is on d5."}

interactive_lesson_stages.title: En Passant from the Other Side
interactive_lesson_stages.instruction_text: En passant works from either side! The black pawn on f5 just moved two squares. Capture it!
interactive_lesson_stages.hints: ["The pawn on f5 just moved from f7 to f5","Your e5 pawn can capture it en passant","Move from e5 to f6 to capture"]
interactive_lesson_stages.feedback_messages: {"correct":"Excellent! You mastered en passant from both sides!","incorrect":"Capture the f5 pawn by moving to f6.","hint":"Move your e5 pawn to f6."}
